<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Tyrone Mings has signed a contract extension with Aston Villa which will keep him at the club until 2024.</p>

<p>The defender, who initially joined on loan from Bournemouth in January 2019, helped play a key part in the club's promotion to the Premier League and subsequent survival last season.</p>

<p>The centre back's performances earned him an England call-up in October 2019 and he was part of the most recent Three Lions' squad for the UEFA Nations League fixtures earlier this month. </p>

<p>Aston Villa have confirmed that Tyrone Mings has signed a contract extension until 2024 </p>
